: double 2 * ;
: square dup * ;
variable counter
42 to counter
symbol red
' double see
' square see
' counter see
' red see
' + see
[: 99 :] see

clear
\ see-compiled shows the compiled body, with fused superwords and their
\ variable operands resolved by name.

variable a  3.0 to a
variable b  4.0 to b

\ two-var, unary-fn, and two-var-mul fusions
: fused  a b f-  a fsq  a b f* ;
' fused see-compiled

\ a literal, a stack+var fusion, and a unary function (f-words fuse; the
\ polymorphic names never do)
: mixed  5.0 a f-  b fsqrt ;
' mixed see-compiled

\ a call to another colon word shows that word's name
: calls  a fsq  fused ;
' calls see-compiled

\ see-compiled on a non-colon word reports it
' a see-compiled

\ local-operand arithmetic fusion: <local> <local> op
: ll-arith | a b | a b f+  a b f-  a b f* ;
' ll-arith see-compiled

\ local-literal arithmetic fusion: <local> <literal> op
: lit-arith | a | a 2.0 f+  a 2.0 f-  a 2.0 f* ;
' lit-arith see-compiled

\ literal-local: commutative <lit> <local> reuse (+, *) and reversed subtract
: rev-arith | a | 2.0 a f+  2.0 a f*  2.0 a f- ;
' rev-arith see-compiled

\ @i index fusion: local index, literal index, and local-array + literal index
: at-local-idx | i | [ 10 20 30 ] i @i ;
' at-local-idx see-compiled
: at-lit-idx  [ 10 20 30 ] 1 @i ;
' at-lit-idx see-compiled
: at-lit-of-local | arr | arr 1 @i ;
' at-lit-of-local see-compiled

\ fusion fires inside a quotation on its own (depth-0) locals
[: | >a >b | a b f* :] see-compiled

clear
\ see-tree expands each colon-word call inline (indented two spaces),
\ recursively, down to primitives; recursive calls print as `name ...`.

: leaf | a b | a b f* a b f+ ;
: mid  | x | x x leaf ;
' mid see-tree

\ recursion is guarded: a self-call prints as a leaf, no infinite expansion
: rec | n | n 1.0 f- rec ;
' rec see-tree

\ non-colon target reports itself
variable v
' v see-tree

clear
\ a quotation header disassembles as [: (span-classified, identical on
\ native and wasm); an else-arm beginning with a colon call is a call
: qmap [ 1 2 3 ] [: 1+ :] map ;
' qmap see-compiled
' qmap see-tree
: helper 1 . ;
: else-call 0 if 2 . else helper then ;
' else-call see-compiled
' else-call see-tree

\ an inline word whose body holds a quotation compiles at call sites as a
\ plain call (a spliced header would have no span); quotation-free inline
\ words still splice
: qinline [ 1 2 3 ] [: 1+ :] map ; inline
: uses-qinline qinline size ;
uses-qinline . cr
' uses-qinline see-compiled
: plain-inline 1+ 2 * ; inline
: uses-plain-inline 5 plain-inline ;
uses-plain-inline . cr
' uses-plain-inline see-compiled
